detailed-desc.p:
i) making a cross between the wheat mutants of the present invention to a species close to durum wheat to make F1 plants;
ii) backcrossing said F1 plants to said species that is close to durum wheat:
iii) repeating backcrossing step until said mutations are integrated into the genome of said species that is close to durum wheat. Special techniques (e.g., somatic hybridization) may be necessary in order to successfully transfer a gene from durum wheat to another species and/or genus. Optionally, such method can be facilitated by molecular markers.
